docs.abstract: The departure of Anthony Noto, Twitter’s chief operating officer, raises concerns about a management vacuum at the social media company.

docs.abstract: Forbes published its first list of the wealthiest cryptocurrency holders, even as recent price declines have shrunk the value of their fortunes.
docs.snippet: Forbes published its first list of the wealthiest cryptocurrency holders, even as recent price declines have shrunk the value of their fortunes.
docs.lead_paragraph: SAN FRANCISCO — The creators of the famous Forbes rich list have made their first attempt to identify the wealthiest people in the virtual currency industry. Yet the list that was published on Wednesday, right after major drops in virtual currency prices, inadvertently also served as a reminder of the fleeting nature of that wealth.

headline.main: Here Are the World’s Virtual Currency Billionaires (or at Least They Were)

docs.snippet: Eric T. Schneiderman filed a suit alleging the studio and its founders violated state and city laws barring gender discrimination and sexual harassment.
docs.lead_paragraph: The fire sale of the Weinstein Company hit a last-minute snag on Sunday, when Eric T. Schneiderman, New York’s attorney general, filed a lawsuit against the studio and its fraternal founders alleging that they repeatedly violated state and city laws barring gender discrimination, sexual harassment, sexual abuse and coercion.
